  "text": "cerevisiae under conditions of peroxisomal induction [CITATION_1] . We now report an attempt to define a peroxisomal membrane targeting signal. We find that a fusion protein containing amino acids 1-267 of PMP47 targets to peroxisomes, whereas one with amino acids 1-199 does not and remains in the cytoplasm or missorts to the nucleus. A fusion containing amino acids 202-420 also appears to sort at low efficiency. However, amino acids 199-267 may not be sufficient; surrounding sequences may be important for sorting or retention of PMP47.",
